DB["Defeat the final boss in any Ascended Raid"]="Vainquez le boss final dans n'importe quel Raid Ascendant."
DB["Defeat the final boss in any Heroic Raid"]="Heroic Raids also allow for flexible group sizes and adjust their difficulty and loot drops to your group size. Heroic Raids require 10 players and allow you to bring up to 25 players.\n\nWearing Bloodforged or PvP gear in Heroic raids will apply the Bloody Debuff to you, massively reducing your damage dealth. Heroic Raids are tuned for players wearing full PvE gear.\n\nHeroic Raid mechanics deal more damage than Flex Raids. You should be prepared to engage in boss mechanics to ensure success!\n\nYou can find a Heroic Raid in World chat or consider forming your own! Guilds are a great place to find dedicated Heroic Raid groups as well.\n\nMany Heroic Raid leaders will require a certain item level to join. You can raise your item level by gearing up in Flex Raids and Heroic Dungeons. It is important to fully enchant your gear with Mystic Enchants that compliment your build before attempting Heroic Raids."
DB["Defeat the final boss in any Mythic Dungeon"]="Vainquez le boss final dans n'importe quel donjon mythique."
DB["Defeat the final boss in any Normal Raid"]="Flex Raids are entry level PvE content that adapt their difficulty to your group size. Flex Raids require 10 players and allow you to bring up to 25 players. Flex Raids are generally easier to complete the more players you have, and the amount of loot dropped is increased based on the group size!\n\nYou will not incur a penalty for wearing Bloodforged or PvP gear in Flex raids, and the difficulty is tuned to allow you to participate without dedicated PvE gear.\n\nFlex Raids leave room for mistakes and are a great place to practice Fight Mechanics without the stress of a mistake causing your entire raid to wipe.\n\nYou can usually find a Flex Raid in World chat, and you can always consider forming your own!\n\nDon't be afraid to dive right into a Flex Raid!"
DB["Defeat the final boss in any end game Normal Dungeon"]="Open the Dungeon Finder and queue for a Random Normal Dungeon or pick any of the available Specific Dungeons.\n\nYou can queue for a dungeon solo, with a partial group or find a full group of players.\n\nWork with your party to fight your way through the dungeon and defeat the final boss of any NORMAL dungeon.\n\nThis quest is incompletable inside of Mythic & Heroic Dungeons."
