DB["Hit N then select Vanity Tab in your Character Advancement menu."]="A powerful item has been added to your Vanity Collection!\n\nThe Scroll of Retreat will teleport you directly to your capital city just like a Hearthstone. And it’s all yours. You just have to claim it!\n\nThe Vanity collection is your own personal vault where account bound items and powerful character enhancements are stored and retrieved. To open your Vanity collection, Hit N to bring up the Character Advancement Menu and then click Vanity.\n\nItems, mounts, cosmetics and toys are found under the Vanity Tab. This is where your Scroll of Retreat is. Click the dropdown menu in the top right and sort by Known, or type Scroll of Retreat into the search bar. Once you find your Scroll of Retreat, select the item, then click Deliver in the left pane.\n\nIf you lose it, or destroy it, you can always deliver it from the Vanity an unlimited amount of times.\n\nThe item will be automatically added to your bags or the Ascension Tab of your Spell Book."
DB["Hit N, then Choose your Path in the upper right section of Character Advancement."]="What stat will you specialize in Hero? Strength, Agility, Intellect or Spirit? Each stat comes with its own unique bonuses and is vital to growing in power."
DB["Hit N, then click the Hero Architect Tab."]="Hit N, or click the scroll icon by your mini map to open up the Character Advancement Menu.\n\nClick the Hero Architect tab near the bottom left of the menu.\n\nScroll through the various builds in the list to the right to find one that interests you or fits your class fantasy. You can change your build anytime, so have fun and pick something that stands out to you. If the build does not match your playstyle you can always repick.\n\nFind a build you would like to play and select \"Choose This Build\" to activate it. You will immediately learn all the required spells and talents, and will automatically learn spells and talents as you level!\n\nIf you are experienced with Ascension, or would like to craft your build from scratch, you can select \"No, I'd like to pick abilities and talents myself.\""
