DB["Learn Apprentice Riding Training. Speak to Kildar in the Valley of Honor within Ogrimmar and select 'I seek to training to ride a steed.'"]="Your journey will call you to new lands and challenges. You could venture to distant lands by foot, but mastering the Riding skill will greatly speed up your journey.\n\nTravel to the Valley of Honor in Orgrimmar and speak with Kildar the Riding Trainer. Kildar will teach you Apprentive Riding for a small sum of gold, allowing you to ride mounts.\n\nYou can find Kildar's location by opening your map and traveling to the quest marker you see in the Valley of Honor inside Orgrimmar.\n\nSpeak to Kildar in then and select \"I seek to training to ride a steed.\"\n\nLearn Apprentice Riding in the training menu. \n\nIf you do not see Apprentice Riding, click the dropdown box and ensure \"Available\" is checked."
DB["Learn Apprentice Riding Training. Speak to Randal Hunter at the Eastvale Logging Camp outside Stormwind in Elwynn Forest and select 'I seek to training to ride a steed.'"]="Your journey will call you to new lands and challenges. You could venture to distant lands by foot, but mastering the Riding skill will greatly speed up your journey.\n\nTravel to Visit Randal Hunter at the Eastvale Logging Camp outside Stormwind in Elwynn Forest to learn Apprentice Riding Training. Randal Hunter will teach you Apprentive Riding for a small sum of gold, allowing you to ride mounts.\n\nYou can find Randal's location by walking outside of Stormwind then opening your map and traveling to the quest marker.\n\nSpeak to Randal in then and select \"I seek to training to ride a steed.\"\n\nLearn Apprentice Riding in the training menu. \n\nIf you do not see Apprentice Riding, click the dropdown box and ensure \"Available\" is checked."
DB["Learn Epic Riding."]="You have learned the art of Riding, but you are still an apprentice. Your mounts have far more potential, but you must advance your training to be able to handle their full speed.\n\nLearn Journeyman Riding to unlock 100% Increased Riding Speed. Most mounts adjust their speed to your riding skill.\n\nYou can learn Journeyman Riding from a Riding Trainer.\n\nYou can usually acquire a Riding Tome: Journeyman Riding from the Auction House or another player cheaper than the cost to train Journeyman Riding at the Trainer."
DB["Learn a Second Specialization."]="Tome of Specialization II will allow you to roll a completely new build on your same character, while still being able to simultaneously switch between the two.\n\nYou can purchase a Tome of Specialization for Gold off the Auction House, Donation Points or Honor Points by visiting any Honor Commendation Master.\n\nOnce you used the Tome of Specialization II, you can then switch from your specialization by three different ways:\n\n - Clicking the Spell in the General Tab of your spellbook called \"Specialization II\"\n - Going into the Character Advancement (N keybind) \n - Typing: \"/cs #\" short for change specialiation, so to switch to specialization II you would type \"/cs 2\"."
DB["Learn from Mojojuju what the not-so-distant future holds for you."]="Apprenez de Mojojuju ce que l’avenir pas si lointain vous réserve."
DB["Learn how to fly through Outland."]="Apprenez à voler à travers l'Outreterre."
