DB["Open the Dungeon Finder by hitting I or click the Green Eye icon in your options menu."]="Dungeons are a great way to gain levels and powerful gear!\n\nNew dungeons become available to queue for as you reach higher levels. You can use the Dungeon Finder solo, or with a group of players.\n\nYou can queue for a dungeon as a Tank, Healer or Damage. You should always be sure you have a build that supports the role you are queueing for. If you have multiple specializations, you can consider creating builds for each role and queueing for more than one role to speed up your queue times!\n\nSelect from the available dungeons by clicking the check box next to the dungeon. Dungeons in Green will be easy for your level, Yellow will be a normal difficulty and Red will be challenging.\n\nYou can queue for one specific dungeon or multiple dungeons at the same time!\n\nSelect the dungeon(s) you wish to queue for and then click Find Group. You will see a Green Eye Icon on your minimap once queued, and you can mouseover the icon to see your queue status. When the group fills up, you will see a pop-up notification and be teleported to the dungeon with your group when everyone accepts."
DB["Open your bags and right click your new Mount."]="It's time to put your Apprentice Riding training to use Hero! Speak with Ogunaro Wolfrunner and purchase a mount!\n\nOnce purchased, right click the mount in your inventory to learn it. \n\nYou can find your known mounts by hitting C to open your character pane, then click the Pets Tab, then Mounts.\n\nDrag the spell for your new mount onto your hotbars so you can quickly mount when you need to travel fast."
