DB["Reach 460 PVE Power by equipping soulbound gear"]="Soulbound gear acquired from Dungeons and Raids always has PvE power. PvE power is often found on Bind on Equip gear and quest reward gear as well!\n\nAcquire a set of PvE gear by completing quests, queuing for Dungeons, killing creatures in No-Risk or through the Auction House. If you add \"PvE\" after your search you will only see gear with PvE power on it.\n\nPvE Power is only active at max level and is critical to progressing through end-game PvE content on Ascension. PvE power increases your damage and healing done while reducing the damage you take.\n\nNormal Dungeons and Flex Raids are ideal content to complete your soulbound PvE gear set. You will not incur a penalty for wearing PvP items in Normal or Flex difficulty, but wearing Bloodforged gear or PvP gear in Heroic difficulty or above Dungeons and Raids will apply the Bloody Debuff, massively reducing your damage done. PvE gear is critical to PvE progression."
