DB["Slay any Faction Leader."]="Attacking a Capital City and defeating its leader awards a powerful spoils of war to all players in the raid.\n\nYou can raid capital cities in No-Risk or High-Risk.\n\nThe best way to find a group to raid a Capital City and defeat a Faction Leader is to pick up the City Siege weekly quest from the Call Board and keep your eye out in World Chat for when a group forms, or if you know a Faction Leader is alive, you can form your own group!\n\nYou can join a Faction Leader raid with PvP or PvE gear. This content is tuned for all players to participate!"
DB["Slay any World Boss."]="When looking for a World Boss group, it is easiest to ask for an invite through World Chat. \n\nWhen a World Boss dies or spawns, it will alert you in the chatbox. When a World Boss is killed they will drop a Treasures of Azeroth Cache stuffed with gear.\n\nYou can use the First-Class-Experimental-Teleporter to get a headstart on the destination after finding your group."
