DB["Speak to Battlemaster Tressa by the Stormwind Call Board. Select No-Risk PvP, No-Risk PvE or High-Risk."]="Hybrid Risk System NPCs can be found in major cities and many neutral cities like Booty Bay and Shattrath. \n\nNo-Risk allows for cross faction PvP with no loot on death.\n\nNo-Risk PvE disables PvP entirely, so you cannot attack or be attacked by other players.\n\nTo opt-in to PvE Mode, choose No-Risk, then select PvE Mode.\n\nHigh-Risk is its own separate phase out in the world, meaning you will not encounter No-Risk players. While in High-Risk, you will drop items from your bag when killed while in Tier 1 zones. If you are killed in a Tier 2 or 3 zone you will also drop equipped loot!\n\nWhen entering High-Risk you will default to a Loyal Member of your faction. You can cast Mercenary for Hire to become neutral, allowing you to attack and be attacked by anyone, but also enable cross faction High-Risk grouping. You can switch between Mercenary and For the Horde or Alliance anytime in a main city by casting the spells in the General Tab of your spell book.\n\nYou can change risk modes at a Hybrid Risk NPC anytime you wish. Talk to a Hybrid Risk NPC and select either No-Risk PvP, No-Risk PvE or High-Risk PvP."
DB["Speak to Blood Keeper Rozok by the Orgrimmar Call Board."]="Hybrid Risk System NPCs can be found in major cities and many neutral cities like Booty Bay and Shattrath. \n\nNo-Risk allows for cross faction PvP with no loot on death.\n\nNo-Risk PvE disables PvP entirely, so you cannot attack or be attacked by other players.\n\nTo opt-in to PvE Mode, choose No-Risk, then select PvE Mode.\n\nHigh-Risk is its own separate phase out in the world, meaning you will not encounter No-Risk players. While in High-Risk, you will drop items from your bag when killed while in Tier 1 zones. If you are killed in a Tier 2 or 3 zone you will also drop equipped loot!\n\nWhen entering High-Risk you will default to a Loyal Member of your faction. You can cast Mercenary for Hire to become neutral, allowing you to attack and be attacked by anyone, but also enable cross faction High-Risk grouping. You can switch between Mercenary and For the Horde or Alliance anytime in a main city by casting the spells in the General Tab of your spell book.\n\nYou can change risk modes at a Hybrid Risk NPC anytime you wish. Talk to a Hybrid Risk NPC and select either No-Risk PvP, No-Risk PvE or High-Risk PvP."
DB["Speak to Doras the Flightmaster at top of the tower next to the Ogrimmar Bank."]="You can find Flightmasters in major cities and quest hubs. Most zones have a Flightmaster that will allow you to quickly travel to and from that zone.\n\nYou can find nearby Flightmasters by hitting the magnifying lense on your mini-map and select Flightmaster.\n\nTo unlock a new Flightpath, you must talk to the Flightmaster. Anytime you travel to a new zone you should look for the Flightmaster in your faction's quest hub."
DB["Speak to the Book of Artisans and learn a profession."]="Professions are an important part of developing your character crafting your identity. Professions fall into two categories, Crafting and Gathering.\n\nMany professions naturally pair well together, like Herbalism and Alchemy or Mining and Blacksmith.\n\nYou can only learn two primary professions, but can learn as many secondary professions as you would like.\n\nSecondary professions include First Aid, Cooking and Fishing.\n\nSpeak to the Beginner's Book of Artisans and pick a profession! You can always unlearn your profession and pick a new one later."
